name: #3: "ComfyUI: Visualising Data Pipelines in Diffusion Models" by Jordan Legg and "The impact of Generative AI on SEO" by James Bavington
description: Whether you like it or not, AI is everywhere! We would love to invite you to our third event to explore two sectors that recently underwent transformative changes: SEO and text-to-image generation.
locationText: Vulcan Works, 34-38 Guildhall Rd, Northampton, NN1 1EW
parkingText: St. John's Multi Storey Car Park

schedule.title: "ComfyUI: Visualising Data Pipelines in Diffusion Models" by Jordan Legg
schedule.description: Explore ComfyUI, a powerful tool for visualising data pipelines in diffusion models. We'll start with an introduction to diffusion models and their significance. Then letâ€™s discover how ComfyUI simplifies the understanding and debugging of complex data flows through practical applications and real-world examples. Highlights include Stable Diffusion 3, SDXL lighting, AI upscaling, and more. Gain insights into how I optimise my diffusion model workflows with this intuitive interface.

schedule.title: "The impact of Generative AI on SEO" by James Bavington
schedule.description: A fast-paced deep-dive into the continually changing landscape of search engine optimisation in the wake of generative AI. From the performance of AI generated content to Google's recently launched AI Overviews , this talk focuses on uses real-world client examples and actionable tips to feed into your day to day as a developer.

guests.name: James Bavington
guests.bio: With a background as a WordPress and Magento developer, James is a highly experienced digital strategist with global clients including GORE-TEX, Reuters, Dorchester Hotel and The Air Ambulance Service.
